theorem Topology.closure_diff_eq_closure_diff {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} (hB : IsClosed (B : Set X)) :
    closure (A \ B) = closure A \ B := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    exact
      Topology.closure_diff_subset_closure_diff
        (X := X) (A := A) (B := B)
  ·
    intro x hx
    rcases hx with ⟨hxClA, hxNotB⟩
    -- We show `x ∈ closure (A \ B)` by the neighbourhood criterion.
    have hxClDiff : x ∈ closure (A \ B) := by
      apply (mem_closure_iff).2
      intro U hUopen hxU
      -- Intersect the neighbourhood with the open complement of `B`.
      have hUBopen : IsOpen (U ∩ Bᶜ) := hUopen.inter hB.isOpen_compl
      have hxUB : x ∈ U ∩ Bᶜ := And.intro hxU hxNotB
      -- Since `x ∈ closure A`, this open set meets `A`.
      have hNonempty : ((U ∩ Bᶜ) ∩ A).Nonempty :=
        (mem_closure_iff).1 hxClA (U ∩ Bᶜ) hUBopen hxUB
      -- Repackage the witness to lie in `U ∩ (A \ B)`.
      rcases hNonempty with ⟨y, ⟨⟨hyU, hyNotB⟩, hyA⟩⟩
      have : (U ∩ (A \ B)).Nonempty := by
        exact ⟨y, And.intro hyU (And.intro hyA hyNotB)⟩
      simpa [Set.inter_assoc, Set.inter_left_comm, Set.inter_comm, Set.diff_eq]
        using this
    exact hxClDiff
